#: cmd/incus/admin_sql.go:29
msgid "Execute a SQL query against the local or global database"
msgstr "UtfûÑr en SQL-frûËga mot den lokala eller globala databasen"

#: cmd/incus/admin_sql.go:30
msgid ""
"Execute a SQL query against the local or global database\n"
"\n"
"  The local database is specific to the cluster member you target the\n"
"  command to, and contains member-specific data (such as the member network\n"
"  address).\n"
"\n"
"  The global database is common to all members in the cluster, and contains\n"
"  cluster-specific data (such as profiles, containers, etc).\n"
"\n"
"  Non-clustered servers still have both local and global databases.\n"
"\n"
"  If <query> is the special value \"-\", then the query is read from\n"
"  standard input.\n"
"\n"
"  If <query> is the special value \".dump\", the command returns a SQL text\n"
"  dump of the given database.\n"
"\n"
"  If <query> is the special value \".schema\", the command returns the SQL\n"
"  text schema of the given database.\n"
"\n"
"  If <query> is the special value \".tables\", the command returns the SQL\n"
"  text tables of the given database.\n"
"\n"
"  This internal command is mostly useful for debugging and disaster\n"
"  recovery. The development team will occasionally provide hotfixes to users "
"as a\n"
"  set of database queries to fix some data inconsistency."
msgstr ""
"KûÑr en SQL-frûËga mot den lokala eller globala databasen\n"
"\n"
"  Den lokala databasen ûÊr specifik fûÑr den klustermedlem som du riktar\n"
"  kommandot till och innehûËller medlemspecifika data (t.ex. medlemmens "
"nûÊtverksadress\n"
"  ).\n"
"\n"
"  Den globala databasen ûÊr gemensam fûÑr alla medlemmar i klustret och "
"innehûËller\n"
"  klusterspecifika data (t.ex. profiler, behûËllare etc.).\n"
"\n"
"Icke-klustrade servrar har fortfarande bûËde lokala och globala databaser.\n"
"\n"
"  Om <query> ûÊr det speciella vûÊrdet \"-\", lûÊses frûËgan frûËn\n"
"  standardinmatningen.\n"
"\n"
"  Om <query> ûÊr det speciella vûÊrdet \".dump\" returnerar kommandot en SQL-"
"textdump\n"
"  av den angivna databasen.\n"
"\n"
"Om <query> ûÊr det speciella vûÊrdet \".schema\" returnerar kommandot SQL-"
"textschemat\n"
"  fûÑr den angivna databasen.\n"
"\n"
"  Om <query> ûÊr det speciella vûÊrdet \".tables\" returnerar kommandot SQL-\n"
"  textabellerna fûÑr den angivna databasen.\n"
"\n"
"  Detta interna kommando ûÊr frûÊmst anvûÊndbart fûÑr felsûÑkning och "
"katastrofûËterstûÊllning\n"
" . Utvecklingsteamet tillhandahûËller ibland snabbkorrigeringar till "
"anvûÊndarna i form av en\n"
"  uppsûÊttning databasfrûËgor fûÑr att ûËtgûÊrda vissa datainkonsekvenser."

#: cmd/incus/exec.go:44
msgid "Execute commands in instances"
msgstr "UtfûÑr kommandon i instanser"

#: cmd/incus/exec.go:45
msgid ""
"Execute commands in instances\n"
"\n"
"The command is executed directly using exec, so there is no shell and\n"
"shell patterns (variables, file redirects, ...) won't be understood.\n"
"If you need a shell environment you need to execute the shell\n"
"executable, passing the shell commands as arguments, for example:\n"
"\n"
"  incus exec <instance> -- sh -c \"cd /tmp && pwd\"\n"
"\n"
"Mode defaults to non-interactive, interactive mode is selected if both stdin "
"AND stdout are terminals (stderr is ignored)."
msgstr ""
"KûÑr kommandon i instanser\n"
"\n"
"Kommandot kûÑrs direkt med exec, sûË det finns inget skal och\n"
"skalmûÑnster (variabler, filomdirigeringar, ...) kommer inte att fûÑrstûËs.\n"
"Om du behûÑver en shellmiljûÑ mûËste du kûÑra shell-programmet\n"
"och skicka shellkommandona som argument, till exempel:\n"
"\n"
"  incus exec <instans> -- sh -c \"cd /tmp && pwd\"\n"
"\n"
"StandardlûÊget ûÊr icke-interaktivt, interaktivt lûÊge vûÊljs om bûËde stdin OCH "
"stdout ûÊr terminaler (stderr ignoreras)."

